---
working_together:
  - title: We're a match. Let's to this.
    reasons:
      - reason: You have a budget and timeline.
      - reason: You value a design process and understand it's role in your project.
      - reason: You need a custom solution to meet your business needs.
      - reason: You need leadership on the technology front to help you solve and implement a working solution for day one.
  - title: Maybe we should see other people.
    reasons:
      - reason: You needed it yesterday.
      - reason: You need a WordPress, Drupal, Joomla, etc. type of CMS site built.
      - reason: You need a developer to make small updates to your exisiting site.
      - reason: You want me to work for free.
      - reason: You're offering equity as payment.
---
<header role="banner" aria-labelledby="site-introduction" class="page__header">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="row">
      <h1 id="site-introduction">
        <b>Oh hello, stranger.</b><br />
        Thanks for stopping by.
      </h1>
      <p class="columns-4__m columns-5__l">Welcome to my little site. I’m a motivated and adaptive innovative thinker who enjoys data-driven, digital design and development. I’m currently helping lead a team of awesome designers and developers at Made By Munsters. Looking for a digital design or development firm? Reachout or learn more about us at <%= link_to 'madebymunsters.com', 'http://madebymunsters.com', target: '_blank' %>.</p>
    </div>
  </div>
</header>
<section role="region" aria-labelledby="working-with-me" class="page__section background--grey">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="row">
      <div class="columns-4__m columns-5__l">
        <h2 id="working-with-me">
          <b>Should we work together?</b><br/>
          Let's see if we are a match.
        </h2>
        <p class="columns-12__l">As a client, finding the right designer or developer for a project is hard. You have to form a trust and be willing to invest in the right person or agency. The same can be said about finding the right clients. Here's how I evaluate whether or not a project is right for me.</p>
      </div>
      <ul class="columns-5__m columns-6__l offset-1__l">
        <% current_page.data.working_together.each do |i| %>
          <li class="columns-4__m columns-6__l">
            <h6><b><%= i.title %></b></h6>
            <ul>
              <% i.reasons.each do |r| %>
                <li><%= r.reason %></li>
              <% end %>
            </ul>
          </li>
        <% end %>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
<section role="region" aria-labelledby="recent-work" class="page__section">
  <div class="container">
    <header class="row">
      <div class="columns-5__l offset-7__l">
        <h2 id="working-with-me" class="float--right">
          <b>A small collection</b><br/>
          of my recent work.
        </h2>
      </div>
    </header>
  </div>
</section>